<seg id=1> Henan Province Holding Discussion Meeting with Foreign Financial Organizations in Beijing </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, Dec. 16. (Reporter Yu Haisheng) The Government of Henan Province held a discussion meeting here today with more than 100 representatives from 88 foreign financial organizations stationed in Beijing, hoping to boost mutual understanding between Henan Province and the international financial world, and to open new financial channels for economic development in Henan. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Chen Yuan, vice president of People's Bank of China, says, in his congratulatory remarks sent to the meeting, that the Chinese Government has decided to re-energize the development of districts in Central and West China, encouraging investments on these districts from enterprises at home and abroad. And the Government also decided, from now on, to put more than 60% of the loans from foreign banks and governments on Central and West China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Cociyet, chairman of foreign financial organizations stationed in Beijing and chief representative of Beijing Representative Office of General Bank of Belgium, says at the meeting that foreign financial organizations stationed in Beijing have the intention to make contributions to the economic construction in Henan and to the development of districts in Central and West China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Li Chengyu, standing vice governor of Henan Province, introduced at the meeting the natural resourses and the economic development of the province. </seg>
<seg id=6> Henan Province not only has the hardwares needed for foreign investors, but has made preferential policies to encourage foreign investments and to develop foreign trade and technological cooperations, he says. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The departments concerned from the Government of Henan Province released at the meeting the programs for foreign economic and technological cooperations, and discussed with the representatives over intentions to cooperate on certain programs. </seg>
</p>
